s also found several times in a male name. From Ann, Anne, we have as nicknames Nan and Nancy"],"variants":[{"name":"Nancy","meanings":["Of uncertain origin. From the 18th century it is clearly used as a pet form of   Ann   (  see  Nan  ), but it may originally have been a similar formation deriving from the common medieval given name   Annis  , a vernacular form of   Agnes .  Nowadays it is an independent name, and was especially popular in America in the 1930s, 40s, and 50s."]},{"name":"Nan","meanings":["Originally a pet form of   Ann   (for the initial <i>N-</i>,  compare  Ned  ). It is now also widely used as a short form of   Nancy ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Anne Delabere was born about 1420, in Hereford, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Thomas Weaver about 1448, in Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1509, in her hometown, at the age of 90."},"et":{"about 1420–1509":"umbes 1420–1509","1413–1503":"1413–1503","1448–1494":"1448–1494","1420–1509":"1420–1509","1448":"1448","1503":"1503","1413":"1413","about 1448":"umbes 1448","about 1503":"umbes 1503","1420":"1420","1494":"1494","about 1420":"umbes 1420","1509":"1509","from 1417 to 1464":"from 1417 to 1464","1418":"1418","Hereford, Herefordshire Unitary Authority, Herefordshire, England":"Hereford, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"England","Presteigne with Discoed, Herefordshire, England":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales","Hereford, Herfordshire, England":"Hereford, Herefordshire, England","Presteigne with Discoed, Radnorshire, Wales":"Presteigne, Radnorshire, Wales","Hereford, Herefordshire, England":"Hereford, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1420–1509":"noin 1420–1509","1413–1503":"1413–1503","1448–1494":"1448–1494","1420–1509":"1420–1509","1448":"1448","1503":"1503","1413":"1413","about 1448":"noin 1448","about 1503":"noin 